---
// ABOUTME: Privacy-focused section highlighting Recall's local-only storage model.
// ABOUTME: Emphasizes zero servers, zero tracking, zero accounts.
---

<section id="privacy" class="px-6 py-20 bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-900">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-center text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-12">Privacy is built in, not bolted on</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-950 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3 flex items-center gap-3">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 shrink-0"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 2a14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0 20 14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0-20"/><path d="M2 12h20"/></svg>
          No Servers
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Recall runs entirely in your browser. Your form data never touches a remote server. No data collection, no cloud storage, no infrastructure to compromise.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-950 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3 flex items-center gap-3">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 shrink-0"><path d="M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z"/><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"/></svg>
          No Tracking
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          We don't track you. No analytics, no beacons, no cookies. We can't know what you save because we never see it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-950 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3 flex items-center gap-3">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 shrink-0"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="m4.9 4.9 14.2 14.2"/></svg>
          No Accounts
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          No login required. No email harvesting. No password to compromise. It's just an extension that works locally on your device.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-950 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3 flex items-center gap-3">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 shrink-0"><path d="M2 3h6a4 4 0 0 1 4 4v14a3 3 0 0 0-3-3H2z"/><path d="M22 3h-6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v14a3 3 0 0 1 3-3h7z"/></svg>
          Open Source
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Audit the code yourself. See exactly how your data is handled. No black boxes, no secrets. MIT-licensed and free to use forever.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 text-center">
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
        <strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Your form data. Your device. Your control.</strong>
      </p>
      <a href="https://github.com/PixelTowers/recall" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-lg border-2 border-gray-800 dark:border-gray-300 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 font-semibold hover:bg-gray-100 dark:hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors">
        Review the code on GitHub
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
